---
description: Security and privacy rules
globs: frontend/**,backend/**,database/**
---

Citizen personal data is used only temporarily for sending the form to AUSEMIO/DPMK.

Do not store permanently:
- phone number
- e-mail address
- photos
- report text
- citizen identity

Do not write citizen personal data to logs.

Technical integration logs may store:
- timestamp
- HTTP status
- success/failure
- technical error code/message without personal data
- selected light point id, if needed

Admin area must be separated from public area.

Admin authentication can be prepared as a simple structure first, but do not expose admin endpoints without protection in future implementation.

Use environment variables for secrets and endpoint configuration.

Do not commit `.env` files with real secrets.

Keep `.env.example` with placeholder values only.
